      "content": "Tariffs are a double-edged sword, and the real impact depends on how they are implemented. Proponents argue they protect domestic industries from unfair foreign competition, which can lead to job growth at home. However, critics point out that tariffs often increase the cost of imported goods, which is then passed on to consumers. Ultimately, they can also lead to retaliatory tariffs from other countries, harming export industries.",
