    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay but if you look at the actual data, the \"resilience\" thing usually just looks like an excuse to let companies avoid competing. if a tariff makes goods more expensive for everyone just to subsidize a dying industry, isn't that fundamentally bad for the country's economic health? it feels like protectionism is just a way to ignore the most efficient way to run an economy.",
