      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are hitting on the core of the argument, which is that protectionism often masks inefficiency. When industries are artificially shielded by tariffs, they lose the necessary pressure to innovate or become cost-effective. This government-enforced complacency is precisely why many economists argue that free markets are superior for overall economic health. The goal of a healthy economy is to produce the best goods at the lowest cost, and tariffs actively work against that principle.",
      "source": "target",
